---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Find Your Best Affiliate Fit";
const description = "Not sure where to start? Explore an easier way to find your optimal path in affiliate marketing, mapped to your current situation.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900 border-b border-gray-800">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white sm:text-5xl">{title}</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-gray-400">If you’re still deciding between niches, programs, platforms, or tools, this page helps you sort your next step more clearly.</p>
      <div class="mt-10">
        <a href="#compare" class="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">Explore your options</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Starting out is prone to distraction.</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-4">Many people focus on the wrong signal first—jumping into complex recurring platforms or high-ticket courses before they even understand who their audience is, resulting in burnout and confusion.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">A better choice usually comes down to fit:</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-400 text-lg space-y-2 mb-8">
        <li>your current level of experience</li>
        <li>the state of your existing content library</li>
        <li>how much time you can dedicate</li>
        <li>clear, logical next steps without skipping ahead</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">What You’ll Find on This Page</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">Use this page as a decision helper when everything still feels too broad. On this page, you’ll find a clearer way to parse through the noise and identify the single path you should be pursuing right now.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Who This Is For</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-4">This page is a good fit if you:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-400 text-lg space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>feel overwhelmed by the amount of information available</li>
        <li>have started but feel like you've taken a wrong turn</li>
        <li>want an honest assessment of what path is viable for your situation</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">This may be less useful if you already know exactly which offer or platform you want and only need a direct signup path.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Why This Direction Matters</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">Instead of trying to learn everything at once, you can focus on the direction that makes the most sense for your current stage. It's about matching intent with practical action.</p>

      <h2 id="compare" class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Choose Your Current Stage</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-700 mb-8">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-b border-gray-700 pb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">If you are utterly new and have no audience...</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">Your first goal is finding a subject you can write or talk about endlessly without burning out. Do not obsess over commission structures yet.</p>
            <a href="/offers/best-affiliate-programs-for-beginners" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 font-medium tracking-wide">View beginner-friendly paths &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div class="border-b border-gray-700 pb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">If you have a defined topic, but no money strategy...</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">You need to align the way you monetize with the way your specific crowd consumes content.</p>
            <a href="/offers/affiliate-programs-by-niche" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 font-medium tracking-wide">Match programs to your niche &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div class="border-b border-gray-700 pb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">If you have traffic, but tiny, erratic payouts...</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">You have a retention or offer-value problem. You need to transition into models that provide deeper value and compounding results.</p>
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <a href="/offers/high-ticket-affiliate-programs" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 font-medium tracking-wide">High-ticket &rarr;</a>
              <span class="text-gray-500">|</span>
              <a href="/offers/recurring-commission-affiliate-programs" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 font-medium tracking-wide">Recurring &rarr;</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="pb-2">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">If you are losing track of links and losing sleep...</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">You lack a streamlined workflow. You don't need new programs; you need infrastructure.</p>
            <a href="/offers/affiliate-tools-for-content-creators" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 font-medium tracking-wide">Find workflow tools &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Trust & Rationale</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">The goal here is not to label one option as universally “best.” It’s to help you compare the right variables so you can choose what fits your niche, workflow, and goals more confidently.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-400 text-lg mb-12">
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">I’m new — is this too advanced?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">Not necessarily. Many of these pages are designed to help you understand the decision first, not force you into a final commitment immediately.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">What if I am still unsure?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">Don't overthink logic models initially. Create 10 pieces of content first on a topic you love, then <a href="/offers/best-affiliate-programs-for-beginners" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">start small</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">Can I change direction later?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">Absolutely. The most successful affiliates routinely pivot their monetization strategies entirely as their audiences mature.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-700 text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Ready to Focus?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-6">Stop jumping from trend to trend and start building a stable, sensible foundation.</p>
        <a href="/programs" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">Find Your Best-Fit Path</a>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Related Resources</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-400 text-lg space-y-3 mb-8">
        <li><a href="/blog/how-to-start-affiliate-marketing-without-getting-overwhelmed" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">How to Start Affiliate Marketing Without Getting Overwhelmed</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/how-to-choose-a-niche-for-affiliate-marketing" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">How to Choose a Niche for Affiliate Marketing More Clearly</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/common-affiliate-marketing-mistakes-beginners-make" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">Common Affiliate Marketing Mistakes Beginners Make Early On</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/affiliate-workflow-for-content-creators" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">How Content Creators Can Build an Affiliate Workflow That Actually Fits</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
